1. The Silo & "Dumb Switchboard" Protocol
The Switchboard Rule: ingestMatrixFile.ts is a "Dumb Orchestrator". It must NEVER contain supplier-specific if/else blocks, unique data transformations, or manual sheet indexing (e.g., [0]).

Interface-Driven Execution: All parsing must be triggered via the mandatory SupplierSilo.parse() method: (sheets: Record<string, unknown[][]>, fileName: string) => Rate[].

Silo Authority: Every supplier folder (e.g., /sfe, /nrg) is the Single Source of Truth for its own tab requirements, metadata extraction, and unpivoting logic.

Registry Integrity: Use src/modules/matrix-parser/supplierRegistry.ts as the sole source of truth. The bridge at src/config/ is deprecated and must not be used.

2. Market Data & Utility Integrity
LPL Purity: LPL (Lubbock Power & Light) is a Utility (TDSP), never a Load Factor.

Normalization Gate: All raw strings from Excel (Zones, Utilities, Load Factors) must pass through a .toUpperCase().trim() normalization gate before registry lookup or persistence to prevent UI pollution (e.g., "Houston" vs "HOUSTON").

Utility Keys: Only use authorized keys from UTILITY_MAP: CENTERPOINT, ONCOR, TNMP, AEP_CENTRAL, AEP_NORTH, and LPL.

AEP & Ghosting Protocol: * Direct Resolution: If specific zone data is available, resolve AEP keys as: "South" -> AEP_CENTRAL, "North/West" -> AEP_NORTH.

Ghosting: If a supplier (e.g., SFE) provides generic "AEP" or combined "CenterPoint/Oncor" data, the Silo must return an array of multiple utility keys to generate distinct "Ghost Records" for each applicable territory.

Load Factor Keys: Only use: LOW, MEDIUM, HIGH.

3. 3D Neon Slab & UI logic (UX/Aesthetic)
Aesthetic: Implement "3D Neon Slab" design using high-contrast Cyan (#00FFFF) and Fuchsia (#FF00FF) accents on Deep Black (#050505).

Slab Shadows: Use thick, hard-offset #000 shadows (e.g., 6px 6px 0px #000) for all cards, inputs, and buttons.

Feedback: Use a Cyan pulsing border during file processing and Fuchsia-bordered alert slabs for errors.

View Switching: "Commission Calculator" and "Matrix Parser" must be separated via the primary navigation.

Component Size: Keep React components under 100 lines for maintainability.

4. Data Integrity & Excel Pipeline
Excel Engine: Use xlsx (SheetJS) for all file decompression.

Thread Isolation: Large file extractions must happen in the Web Worker (xlsxIngest.worker.ts) to prevent UI lag.

Standard Units: All internal math and storage use kWh and $/kWh.

Naming: Variables representing money must include a unit suffix (e.g., ratePerKwh, marginPerKwh).

Date Uniformity: All startDate and effectiveDate values must be stored in YYYY-MM-DD string format.

5. Technical Guardrails
TypeScript: Strictly prohibit any. Use interfaces from src/types/market-data.ts.

Offline-First: All logic and persistence (IndexedDB/PowerToolsDB) must be 100% local.

State Resets: Use filterSignature keys to ensure clean UI resets during new file ingestion.

Safety Guards: Implement immediate feedback (e.g., "Missing Decimal") for any calculated field.